{
  "_comment": [
    "Segment spec for the Web Store demo video. The build script reads this and",
    "produces the final cut. Frame numbers are sequential decode-frames (what a",
    "video player like QuickTime shows in its frame counter), NOT PTS-based.",
    "Sources are variable-frame-rate (VFR) — frame timestamps are NOT evenly",
    "spaced — so we look up the exact PTS for each decoded frame index via",
    "ffprobe rather than dividing by an effective_fps. ffmpeg's `trim` then cuts",
    "by those real PTS times.",
    "",
    "To recompute time_range_s after editing frame_range, run:",
    "  ffprobe -v error -select_streams v:0 -show_entries frame=pts_time \\",
    "    -of csv=p=0 SOURCE | awk 'NR==FRAME {print}'",
    "",
    "linger_s controls how long the last frame holds before the fade-through-",
    "black transition starts. Default 0.3s. Bump per segment to slow a beat down."
  ],

  "sources": {
    "screen-settings.mov": {
      "duration_s": 31.512,
      "nb_frames": 713,
      "advertised_fps": 60,
      "vfr": true
    },
    "screen-final1.mov": {
      "duration_s": 72.177,
      "nb_frames": 2220,
      "advertised_fps": 60,
      "vfr": true
    },
    "screen-delete-api.mov": {
      "duration_s": 16.625,
      "nb_frames": 466,
      "advertised_fps": 60,
      "vfr": true
    }
  },

  "transitions": {
    "type": "fadeblack",
    "duration_s": 1.0,
    "default_linger_s": 0.3
  },

  "title_card": {
    "text": "Hover Street View for RideWithGPS",
    "font_size": 140,
    "duration_s": 3
  },

